annotationA: UV radiation resistance-associated gene protein; UV-resistance associated gene (Uvrag) regulates autophagy and vesicle trafficking with Atg6 and class C vaculoar protein sorting complexes. With Atg6 and Pi3K59F, Uvrag forms a PI3K(III) complex and plays roles in receptor downregulation and the establishment of proper cell polarity. It is also critical for proper organ rotation during development by controlling receptor endocytosis and subsequent degradation
